With Office 365, you can share and grant permission to Office files with members of your Yammer group without having to leave the Office app\.

__Share files__

In an Office app like Word, Excel, or PowerPoint:

1. From a file you'd like to share, select __Share__\.
2. Select the permission settings you want\.
3. Type in the name of the Yammer group you want to share with — the name should automatically populate from your organization's directory\.
4. Type a message to give context or information for your file\.
5. Select __Send__\.

__Share from anywhere in Office 365__

1. To share straight from Word, PowerPoint or Excel, click on the __Share person__ icon in the upper\-right corner\.
2. To share from SharePoint or OneDrive, right\-click on the file and click __Share__, or select the file and click on __Share__ at the top\.
3. To share from Outlook, forward the email\.
4. Type in the name of the Yammer group you want to share with\. The name should populate from your organization’s directory\.
5. Select the right permission \(__Edit__ or __View__\)\.
6. Write a message to the group to give members context, then click __Share__ or __Send__\.

__Use group resources__

Get projects up and running with shared resources in a Yammer group\.

Under __Office 365 Resources__, you'll see different services and apps to help you and your community get started:

- Manage content and knowledge in a group __SharePoint Document Library__
- Build a __SharePoint Site__ for your group
- Manage notetaking in a shared __OneNote__
- Organize tasks for the group in __Planner__

[https://www\.microsoft\.com/en\-us/videoplayer/embed/116ee304\-df0a\-4f7c\-8c23\-bbd085f8cea5?autoplay=false](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/videoplayer/embed/116ee304-df0a-4f7c-8c23-bbd085f8cea5?autoplay=false)

__Use shared group resources__

In the right rail below Office 365 Resources, click on the service or app you want to access:

1. Manage content and knowledge in a group __SharePoint Document Library__\.
2. Build a __SharePoint Site__ for your group\.
3. Manage notetaking in a shared __OneNote__\.
4. Manage tasks for the group in __Planner__\.
